headlines.description: — Jaden Ivey scored 34 points and Cade Cunningham had 32 points and 11 assists to lead the Detroit Pistons to their first home win since January, 118-112 over the Brooklyn Nets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ivey, Cunningham lead Pistons to first home win since January, 118-112 over Brooklyn

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards matched his season high with 44 points, made a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 1:11 to go and came up with a spectacular block at the buzzer to give the short-handed...
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 44, has spectacular last-second block as Wolves beat Pacers 113-111

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 35 points, 11 rebounds and 11 assists to become the second NBA player to record five consecutive 30-point triple-doubles, and the Dallas Mavericks rallied past the Miami Heat 114-108 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic records fifth consecutive 30-point triple-double in Mavs' 114-108 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 35 points, Grayson Allen added 26 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Toronto Raptors 120-113 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 35, Grayson Allen adds 26 and the Suns beat the Raptors 120-113

headlines.description: — Sometimes, Nikola Jokic's triple-double is as meaningful as it is magical.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic's triple-double helps Nuggets to season sweep of Celtics with 115-109 win

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry's troublesome right ankle buckled again, and that hurt as much as anything for the Golden State Warriors in yet another late-game defeat.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan delivers in final minute, Curry goes down as Bulls beat Warriors 125-122

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored 31 points, including the go-ahead dunk with 7.7 seconds remaining, and the Sacramento Kings beat the San Antonio Spurs 131-129 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis’ dunk with 7.7 seconds left sends Kings past Spurs 131-129
